<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.3B1/5a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-02T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 2,
                                        1919—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>3310. Can you inform Department of any reason why Brazil is not signatory
                            of the Arms Traffic Convention?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>